        "created_at": "2025-10-07T17:46:43.687Z",
        "cooked": "<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/2/a/2a6bc499eb199e87e9068638c8201ab771898091.png\" data-download-href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/2a6bc499eb199e87e9068638c8201ab771898091\" title=\"image\"><img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/2/a/2a6bc499eb199e87e9068638c8201ab771898091_2_262x500.png\" alt=\"image\" data-base62-sha1=\"63gWCNAa7QvrUnkYS6K78PcH8EV\" width=\"262\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/2/a/2a6bc499eb199e87e9068638c8201ab771898091_2_262x500.png, https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/2/a/2a6bc499eb199e87e9068638c8201ab771898091_2_393x750.png 1.5x, https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/2/a/2a6bc499eb199e87e9068638c8201ab771898091.png 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"181717\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">image</span><span class=\"informations\">432×822 33.9 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>\n<p>Problem:</p>\n<p>As you can see, I am using Signal after making it smaller(and portrait), and it helps save me a lot of space on my display, but the ui is so bad, and the settings are completely unusable if I am using it like this. I have to manually resize and make it landscape for me to be able to navigate the settings.</p>\n<p>Solution:</p>\n<p>If it is being used in portrait mode, make it similar to the mobile ui most people are familiar with it and will agree that it’s betting in this situation.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>The bar on the left is too thick and unnecessary; either make it small or move it to the top, making it a small bar containing other chats and the rest in the main menu.</li>\n<li>Make the settings usable in this mode. Please make it usable. I really don’t care what method you guys use, but make it usable.</li>\n</ol>",
